installing
----------

    $ sudo apt-get install supervisor

start-stop
----------

sudo service supervisor start|stop|restart


adding applications
-------------------

- add a config file for each app under /etc/supervisor/conf.d/ with a .conf extension

e.g. my_app.conf

[program:my_app]
command=/usr/local/bin/my_app
autostart=true
autorestart=true
stderr_logfile=/var/log/my_app.err.log
stdout_logfile=/var/log/my_app.out.log

config
------
- autostart: true|false|unexpected
    unexpected tells supervisor to only restart the program if it exits with an unexpected error code (something other than 0 or 2)

environment variables
---------------------

    [program:example]
    command=/usr/bin/example --loglevel=%(ENV_LOGLEVEL)s

    # in the above %(ENV_LOGLEVEL) would expand to the environment variable LOGLEVEL

supervisorctl
-------------

- interactive mode
    
    $ supervisorctl
    supervisor> 

    supervisor> help

- look for any new or changed program config

    $ supervisorctl reread

- apply changes

    $ supervisorctl update

    
href: http://supervisord.org/configuration.html#program-x-section-settings

